  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>For <a href="http://openhatch.org/search/">http://openhatch.org/search/</a> this is a simple fix.  Next to the "add a bug 
tracker" link, put "add a project".  (See page1.png, attached.)

For <a href="http://openhatch.org/guide/">http://openhatch.org/guide/</a> it's a bit more complicated.  I think we need an 
extra tab "add your project" (in addition to "Represent your project", "Give 
newcomers direction", "Use proven social strategies") which should be the 
default tab highlighted (currently the default tab is "Represent your project".  
This can link to both the add a tracker page, and 
<a href="http://openhatch.org/+portfolio/editor/">http://openhatch.org/+portfolio/editor/</a>

It's worth noting that you need to log in to view 
<a href="http://openhatch.org/+portfolio/editor/">http://openhatch.org/+portfolio/editor/</a>  We have room to say this on the /guide 
page, not sure if it makes sense to add a warning to the /search page, which 
will have a terse link.  Alternatively we could have a custom page before you're 
directed to log in.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
